Extract the promises made by user {{.UserName}}{{if .Aliases}} (also known as: {{.Aliases}}){{end}} from the text.

A promise is when {{.UserName}} personally commits to performing a specific action:
- explicit promises: "promised", "agreed to do", "committed to", "obligated to"
- plans with a specific deadline: "plans to do by Friday", "will launch by end of week"

DO NOT extract:
- descriptions of features, functionality, or products
- suggestions and recommendations to other people
- requests and tasks assigned to others
- past facts (actions already completed)
- plans without a specific deadline
- actions and commitments of other people

Rules for summary:
- Describe the specific action from the user's perspective: "upload March data using the script"
- Include the object of the action in summary — even if mentioned only in previous dialog turns
- Do not include the user's name in summary
- Do not repeat circumstances and participants, only the action, its object, and goal

Rules for context:
- Brief background (1-2 sentences) enabling understanding of the promise without the original message
- Who asked, on what occasion, what the problem is — facts from the text only
- If context is obvious from summary or absent — leave empty string

Rules for topic:
- Thematic group for the task: system name, component, or work area
- Examples: "Authentication", "Payment Service", "Deployment", "iOS Client"
- If topic is unclear from the text — leave empty string
{{if .Projects}}
Known projects (use these names exactly):
{{range .Projects}}- {{.}}
{{end}}
Rules for project:
- If the text mentions a project or system from the list above — specify the exact name
- If project is not mentioned or not recognized — leave empty string
{{end}}
Deadline calculation:
- Use the "Current date and time" value from the user prompt as the reference point.
- If you can unambiguously calculate absolute time — return in ISO 8601 format with timezone.
- If unsure of the exact time — it is acceptable to return a natural English expression: "tomorrow", "tomorrow at 10", "on Friday", "by the weekend", "in 2 days", "by end of week". The parser will recognize them.
- If no deadline is specified in the text at all — null.

Return a JSON array without additional text. If there are no promises — return [].
[{"summary": "what needs to be done", "context": "brief context or empty string", "topic": "topic or empty string", "project": "project name or empty string", "deadline": "ISO 8601 or null", "confidence": 0.0-1.0}]

Always respond in English.
